So, why choose us? Because Vention means 20+ years of transformation and software excellence

Vention exists to connect business leaders with the expertise they need to innovate boldly, grow faster, and scale smarter.

Sergei Kovalenko
Co-founder & CEO

Based in New York with a background in microelectronics and software engineering, he focuses on applying software solutions to help scale disruptive startups and fast-growing companies worldwide. In addition to leading the strategic vision for Vention’s service provision model, he is passionate about investing in and partnering with early-stage tech companies.

Sergei is an investor through TechLaunch, DreamIt Ventures, Arc Angel Fund, and Scout Ventures — and in 2014, co-founded Braavo Capital, a company focused on funding and growing mobile app and game companies.

Andrey Kulgachev
Co-founder & CIO

A Vention cofounder, Andrey oversees the company's IT administration department as well as related business operations and internal systems. 

Andrey continues to play an integral role as the company rapidly expands, leading day-to-day operational activities, strategic planning, and community activities to support uninterrupted, uncompromised growth.

Marc Karasu
CMO

Marc has over 20 years of experience as a growth marketer, helping to transform B2B and B2C brands and scale disruptive initiatives. 

As CMO, Marc leads Vention’s three marketing divisions: Growth, Design, and Brand, defining the department’s collective strategy and associated goals on a global scale.

Previous leadership roles with tech innovators, including Yahoo!, Betterment, and Ellevest, complemented by hands-on creative development, media buying, and channel optimization at renowned brand agencies such as Chiat/Day and BBH have shaped Marc’s strategic approach to marketing objectives, consistently resulting in the generation of efficient user growth; brand awareness; audience engagement; and revenue.

Glyn Roberts
CTO of Digital Solutions

With over 20 years of experience delivering software projects and leading technology teams across the UK and Europe, Glyn is a seasoned IT professional with deep expertise in technology stacks, cloud solutions, and optimizing distributed teams. Known for his strategic insight, he is often sought after as an engineering advisor, interim CTO, and mentor, particularly by tech companies developing innovative products.

Glyn is also an active voice in the tech community, serving as a prominent member of CTO Craft and founding CTO Portugal, fostering collaboration and knowledge-sharing among technology leaders.

Mikhail Linnik
VP of Software Engineering

Mikhail brings over 20 years of experience in delivery leadership, technical management, and organizational development, with a strong track record of building high-performing teams and scaling operations globally.

As VP of Software Engineering at Vention, he leads the transformation of our global delivery organization, overseeing ten delivery centers and the Delivery Management Office. He focuses on strengthening collaboration, driving operational excellence, and aligning delivery with key business functions like marketing, finance, and talent growth. A key priority for Mikhail is building deep technological and domain expertise across the company to support a future-ready delivery model based on specialization and innovation.

Before Vention, he held leadership roles at top engineering firms, where he consistently delivered results across strategic, operational, and technical areas. His hands-on approach and broad expertise continue to shape Vention’s growth as a world-class tech partner.

Gennady Andreyev
Delivery Director

With over 15 years in engineering, Gennady has advanced from software engineer to business unit head. As the leader of Vention’s software development services, he oversees the delivery of cutting-edge solutions across the company’s global infrastructure, ensuring the highest standards of quality and innovation in every project.

His expertise in applied mathematics and physics and hands-on technical experience enable him to tackle complex challenges, build high-performing teams, and deliver compelling results for clients worldwide.

Hanna Volchek
VP of Talent

With over 18 years of experience in talent management, Hanna has a proven track record of attracting, growing, and retaining top professionals.

As the head of Vention’s talent growth unit, she oversees acquisition, HR, communications, and learning and development, aligning initiatives with global objectives to drive growth and continuous improvement.

Her leadership spans FMCG, industrial markets, and pharmaceuticals, where she led recruitment efforts and workforce planning. Hanna’s expertise delivers innovative talent solutions that strengthen organizations and empower teams to excel.

And, of course, it’s our 3,000+ strong team that powers it all. Engineers, designers, QA experts, project managers, HR professionals, engagement managers, and marketers — each plays a vital role in turning your vision into visionary results.

Ventioneers are at home in every time zone...

...supported to create, innovate, and thrive

We take care of each other

  • Personalized career pathways: Our self-developed platform tracks and supports individual goals.

  • Growth-focused engagement: Vention’s engagement center recommends skills needed to advance careers.

  • Support at every step: Dedicated HR representatives provide guidance and handle day-to-day needs.

  • Ongoing development: We offer regular one-on-ones, satisfaction assessments, and health checks for all team members.

We learn and help others learn

  • EDU community: Our employee-driven learning community spans 30+ tech paths, including .NET, Python, and blockchain, with niche groups for VR, game development, and AI.

  • Sharing (knowledge) is caring: Meetups, tech talks, dev2dev sessions, and trainer awards keep innovation thriving and ideas flowing.

  • Fun beyond the code: Speaking clubs and hobby channels — covering everything from pets to finance — help our team recharge, connect, and spark creativity.

We give back to grow forward

  • Pledge 1% members: We dedicate 1% of our time to community initiatives like volunteering and cleanups.

  • Eco-conscious offices: Reusable materials, water-saving measures, and hybrid work models help us minimize our footprint.

  • A socially responsible company: We partner with leading nonprofit organizations to drive lasting humanitarian impact worldwide — advocating for mental health, providing global aid, and empowering the next generation of tech leaders.

  • Commitment to community: Through initiatives like the In:Vention Incubator, scholarships, and mentorships, we empower the next wave of tech talent.

All these steps have made us an employer of choice — a choice our team makes with pride and confidence every day.
